TITLE: Implementing Auto-Size Text Field in React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a text field that automatically resizes to fit its content using the TextField component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shopify/polaris/blob/main/polaris.shopify.com/content/components/selection-and-input/text-field.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {TextField} from '@shopify/polaris';
import React from 'react';

export function TextFieldExample() {
  const [value, setValue] = React.useState('');

  const handleChange = React.useCallback(
    (newValue) => setValue(newValue),
    [],
  );

  return (
    <TextField
      label="Product name"
      value={value}
      onChange={handleChange}
      autoSize
      autoComplete="off"
    />
  );
}
```

